<TEXTAREA NAME="ReplyMessage" ROWS=10 COLS=45 WRAP="VIRTUAL">[QUOTE]Originally posted by Dazl:
[B]Id agree that the res stick is similar to the manastone.

Im a second rate cleric. Ive had the pearl since xmas, and despite 2 long attempts to camp ragefire, i gave up when i realise how obsessive you'd have to be to attempt to stay awake for 3 days, or organise someone to hold to camp while you sleep.

If no-one was obsessed enough to do that, then you could walk into sol-b, clear the FG and find Zordak up, then complete the epic.

You cant, too many people (at least on my server) feign there or sit their cleric in the lair for as long as it takes. In general this is seen as claiming the spawn, and id not like to walk over anyone doing that, as im not a confrontational type of cleric.

After reading Verants comments, i never once saw them mention why this Epic quest would be fun. If its not fun, why does it have a place in a game ?

A game is entertainment ? or has it merely degraded to a time-sink now ?

For me it has.

For 2 weeks no EQ for me. A guild mate wants to play my cleric, and that would be fine, but i really want to cancel the account to give some *noticable* (affects their income) feedback to Verant.

Too many people leave the account active in case the want to play again.
[/B][/QUOTE]

</TEXTAREA>
